OL,3,CMillions missing out on energy savings
OL,4,Cas Ofgem price cap falls
OL,6,FThe energy price cap is calculated
OL,7,Ffour times a year by the energy
OL,8,Fregulator Ofgem - in February, May,
OL,9,FAugust and November.
OL,11,FOfgem does the calculations based on a
OL,12,Fvariety of factors like wholesale
OL,13,Fenergy costs, policy and operating
OL,14,Fcosts, and value added tax.
OL,16,FSome energy-saving tips if you're
OL,17,Fthinking of switching:
OL,19,FCustomers' energy debts for the UK now
OL,20,Ftotal around #4 billion - an all-time
OL,21,Fhigh.
